# Data Sampling

![../60-Meta-Attachments/b32a29855f826f81f2a274924fa4484f.png](data:image/png;base64,)

- Actual A/D process involves sampling, which represents the time domain resolution of the analogue signal.
- The more often you sample, the more accurate the data, but the more storage space required.

## Signal Level and Noise

- Amplify signal to improve accuracy
- But noise is also amplified
- So averaging reduces the amplified noise
  ![../60-Meta-Attachments/b8076674e6a0ba090b11f862dc3e885f.png](data:image/png;base64,)
